verses.roman:
śrī-mādhava-purīra saṅge śrī-raṅga-purī
pūrve āsiyāchilā teṅho nadīyā-nagarī

synonyms: śrī-mādhava-purīra saṅge—with Śrī Mādhavendra Purī; śrī-raṅga-purī—Śrī Raṅga Purī; pūrve—formerly; āsiyāchilā—came; teṅho—he; nadīyā-nagarī—to the city of Nadia.
translation: Śrī Raṅga Purī had formerly gone to Navadvīpa with Śrī Mādhavendra Purī, and he therefore remembered the incidents that took place there.
